Marco Reus has warned Germany that Scotland will be no pushovers when the two sides meet in their opening Euro 2016 qualifier in Dortmund on Sunday.

Gordon Strachan's men go into the match against the world champions on a year-long unbeaten run, while the hosts went down 4-2 to Argentina in a friendly on Wednesday.

Scotland have not qualified for a major tournament for 16 years, but Reus backed them to qualify from their group this time.

