'Scotland definitely have a chance of finishing in second place. With Darren Fletcher they have a real leader, up front they have quick and dangerous players. You have to be patient against them.'

Germany's goalkeeping coach Andreas Kopke had words of praise for Scotland goalkeeper Allan McGregor, describing him as 'experienced' and 'consistent if unspectacular'.

'That he is a regular in the Premier League speaks for itself,' he added.

